# Writing style: no AI tells

When writing any prose (documentation, READMEs, comments, commit messages,
PR descriptions, user-facing copy):

- Never use: delve, tapestry, showcase, underscore, meticulous, commendable,
  realm, game-changer, seamless, groundbreaking, cutting-edge, leverage,
  harness, unveil, revolutionize, transformative, testament, pivotal,
  intricate, vibrant, boasts, landscape (figurative), navigating (figurative).
- No em-dashes. Use commas, periods, or parentheses.
- No "not just X, but Y" constructions. Assert directly.
- Write "is/are/has" instead of "serves as / stands as / boasts / represents".
- Mix sentence lengths; never three similar-length sentences in a row.
- No throat-clearing openers ("It's worth noting") or closing bows
  ("In conclusion").
- Concrete over abstract: numbers, names, examples. Name sources; never
  "studies show" without which study.
- Take positions with reasons. No symmetric hedging.
- Before finishing prose, re-scan for em-dashes and banned words; fix them.
